<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,259,1042]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,439,465]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Description.</emphasis>
Burrowing specimen; size, 4.5 × 2 × 
<quantity box="[774,854,439,466]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="1.2">1.2 cm</quantity>
. Papillae or oscules not observed. Color 
<emphasis box="[1316,1393,440,465]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">in vivo</emphasis>
not recorded—light purple color in ethanol. Consistency is slightly friable.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,259,1042]" box="[199,1396,511,537]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,511,537]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Skeleton.</emphasis>
Bundles of tylostyles disposed perpendicular toward the surface (
<figureCitation box="[1047,1152,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1360,1384]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,813,1342]" captionTargetId="figure-219@25.[151,1435,813,1342]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 18. Cliona dioryssa (CNPGG-2165), skeleton and spicules: A. transversal section of the skeleton; B. tylostyles and spirasters. Cliona flavifodina (CNPGG-2386), habitus and spicules: C. burrowing habit (into a piece of coral); D. tylostyles and spirasters, arrows pointing to spirasters (one zoomed in). Scale bars: A–B and D (including zoomed-in) = 25 µm; C = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5454416" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5454416/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 18A</figureCitation>
). Spirasters scattered.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,259,1042]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,547,573]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Spicules.</emphasis>
Megascleres: Tylostyles smooth, in a large size range (
<figureCitation box="[928,1032,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1411,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-441@24.[151,1435,1411,1940]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 17. Cliona dioryssa (de Laubenfels, 1950) (CNPGG-2165), SEM spicules: A. tylostyle; B. spirasters II. C. spirasters I. Scale bars: A = 100 µm, B–C = 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5454414" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5454414/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 17A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1044,1093,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1360,1384]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,813,1342]" captionTargetId="figure-219@25.[151,1435,813,1342]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 18. Cliona dioryssa (CNPGG-2165), skeleton and spicules: A. transversal section of the skeleton; B. tylostyles and spirasters. Cliona flavifodina (CNPGG-2386), habitus and spicules: C. burrowing habit (into a piece of coral); D. tylostyles and spirasters, arrows pointing to spirasters (one zoomed in). Scale bars: A–B and D (including zoomed-in) = 25 µm; C = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5454416" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5454416/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">18B</figureCitation>
), 222– 
<emphasis box="[1171,1234,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">253.2</emphasis>
(25)–292.6/2.9– 
<emphasis box="[1422,1436,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">4</emphasis>
(1.5)–5.8 µm, with a rounded tyle (some mucron shape) 5– 
<emphasis box="[832,867,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">6.8</emphasis>
(2)–8.5 µm width. Microscleres: Spiraster I (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1411,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-441@24.[151,1435,1411,1940]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 17. Cliona dioryssa (de Laubenfels, 1950) (CNPGG-2165), SEM spicules: A. tylostyle; B. spirasters II. C. spirasters I. Scale bars: A = 100 µm, B–C = 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5454414" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5454414/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 17B</figureCitation>
), stout spirasters with very thin and small, simple thorns, 8.2– 
<emphasis box="[892,920,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">15</emphasis>
(5)–21.3/ up to 6 µm. Spirasters II (
<figureCitation box="[1321,1423,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1411,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-441@24.[151,1435,1411,1940]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 17. Cliona dioryssa (de Laubenfels, 1950) (CNPGG-2165), SEM spicules: A. tylostyle; B. spirasters II. C. spirasters I. Scale bars: A = 100 µm, B–C = 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5454414" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5454414/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 17C</figureCitation>
), thin spirasters, longer and slender than the previous category, with very thin and small thorns (bifurcated or trifurcated tips); 22– 
<emphasis box="[324,373,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">39.5</emphasis>
(5)–60/ up to 2 µm (
<figureCitation box="[607,710,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1411,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-441@24.[151,1435,1411,1940]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 17. Cliona dioryssa (de Laubenfels, 1950) (CNPGG-2165), SEM spicules: A. tylostyle; B. spirasters II. C. spirasters I. Scale bars: A = 100 µm, B–C = 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5454414" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5454414/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 17C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
