<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,150,393]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
The color 
<emphasis box="[314,389,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">in vivo</emphasis>
is described as bright orange in de 
<bibRefCitation author="Laubenfels, M. W. de" box="[783,989,150,177]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 154" refId="ref78070" refString="Laubenfels, M. W. de (1950) The Porifera of the Bermuda Archipielago. Transactions of the Zoological Society of London, 27, 1 - 154. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1950. tb 00227. x" type="journal article" year="1950">Laubenfels (1950)</bibRefCitation>
and yellow to orange in 
<bibRefCitation author="Rutzler, K." box="[1265,1432,151,177]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="32" refId="ref80398" refString="Rutzler, K. (1974) The Burrowing Sponges of Bermuda. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 165, 32. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.165" type="journal article" year="1974">Rützler (1974)</bibRefCitation>
. Unfortunately, we do not know the color 
<emphasis box="[609,684,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">in vivo</emphasis>
of our material since it was inside a piece of coral, which was fixed in ethanol. Thus, the specimen examined was not found until laboratory analysis. Further, the light purple color of the tissue in ethanol differs from the material of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="de Laubenfels" baseAuthorityYear="1950" box="[693,821,259,285]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Cliona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clionaida" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="dioryssa">
<emphasis box="[693,821,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">C. dioryssa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rutzler, K." box="[978,1145,259,285]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="32" refId="ref80398" refString="Rutzler, K. (1974) The Burrowing Sponges of Bermuda. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 165, 32. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.165" type="journal article" year="1974">Rützler (1974)</bibRefCitation>
. Based on spiculation, we believe that our material can be classified as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="de Laubenfels" baseAuthorityYear="1950" box="[655,782,295,321]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Cliona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clionaida" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="dioryssa">
<emphasis box="[655,782,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">C. dioryssa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species has been recorded from the 
<taxonomicName authority="Islands" authorityName="Islands" box="[1247,1436,295,321]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chondropsidae" genus="Strongylacidon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="bermuda">Bermuda Islands</taxonomicName>
(de 
<bibRefCitation author="Laubenfels, M. W. de" box="[195,387,330,357]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 154" refId="ref78070" refString="Laubenfels, M. W. de (1950) The Porifera of the Bermuda Archipielago. Transactions of the Zoological Society of London, 27, 1 - 154. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1950. tb 00227. x" type="journal article" year="1950">Laubenfels 1950</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Rutzler, K." box="[400,548,331,357]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="32" refId="ref80398" refString="Rutzler, K. (1974) The Burrowing Sponges of Bermuda. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 165, 32. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.165" type="journal article" year="1974">Rützler 1974</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[614,682,331,357]" name="Brazil" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Muricy, G. &amp; Lopes, D. A. &amp; Hajdu, E. &amp; Carvalho, M. D. S. &amp; Moraes, F. C. &amp; Klautau, M. &amp; Menegola, C. &amp; Pinheiro, U." box="[698,917,331,357]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref79280" refString="Muricy, G., Lopes, D. A., Hajdu, E., Carvalho, M. D. S., Moraes, F. C., Klautau, M., Menegola, C. &amp; Pinheiro, U. (2011) Catalogue of Brazilian Porifera. Serie livros 46. Museu Nacional, Rio de Janeiro, 300 pp." type="book" year="2011">
Muricy 
<emphasis box="[791,849,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first record of the species for the GoM, thus widening its distribution.
</paragraph>
